article.headline: Wis.-Green Bay 80, South Dakota St. 48
article.story: GREEN BAY, Wis. (AP) -- Mike Schachtner scored a game-high 18 points and Ryan Tillema returned from a six-game absence to score 14 off the bench as Wisconsin-Green Bay routed South Dakota State 80-48 Saturday night. The Phoenix (5-5) won its third straight game and has reached the 80-point mark in all three victories. Wis.-Green Bay didn't commit a turnover as it built a 34-16 halftime lead and then shot 58.3 percent from the field in the second half to put the game away. The Jackrabbits (2-10) were led by Matt Caldwell's 14 points. Jose Frias scored 13 and Blake Yackley added 12. Schachtner followed up a 36-point performance in a win over Chicago State on Tuesday with 18 points and six rebounds Saturday. Ryan Evanochko added 13 points for Wis.-Green Bay.
